43 (B) In all other cases, the adjusted base year assessed value of the homestead as
44 calculated in the taxable year immediately preceding the current year, including any
45 final determination of value on appeal pursuant to Code Section 48-5-311.
46 (7) "Substantial property change" means any increase or decrease in the assessed value
47 of a homestead derived from additions or improvements to, or the removal of real
48 property from, the homestead which occurred after the year in which the base year
49 assessed value is determined for the homestead. The assessed value of the substantial
50 property changes shall be established following any final determination of value on
51 appeal pursuant to Code Section 48-5-311.
52 (b)(1) Subject to the limitations provided in this section, each resident of the City of
53 Cartersville independent school district is granted an exemption on that person's
54 homestead from ad valorem taxes in an amount equal to the amount by which the current
55 year assessed value of that homestead, including any final determination of value on
56 appeal pursuant to Code Section 48-5-311, exceeds its previous adjusted base year
57 assessed value.
58 (2) Except as provided for in subsection (c) of this section, no exemption provided for
59 in this subsection shall transfer to any subsequent owner of the property, and the assessed
60 value of the property shall be as provided by law.
61 (c) No person shall receive the exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section unless
62 such person or person's agent files an application with the governing authority of the City of
63 Cartersville as will enable the governing authority to make a determination regarding the
64 initial and continuing eligibility of such person for such exemption; provided, however, that
65 any person who had previously applied for a homestead exemption, was allowed such
66 homestead exemption for the 2025 tax year, and remains eligible for a homestead exemption
67 for that same homestead property in the 2026 tax year shall be automatically allowed the
68 exemption granted under subsection (b) of this section for that homestead without further
69 application. The governing authority shall provide application forms for this purpose.
